nice_json.internal_utils.AssortedUtils

type
class
Few utilities to make my life simpler.

Static Methods

array_from_iterator<T>(it : Iterator<T>) : Array<T>

Return Array from Iterator

compare_string(a : String, b : String) : Int

Returns -1 if a < b, 0 if a = b, 1 if a > b. Used in Array.sort.

hash_to_key_value_iterable(s : Hash<Dynamic>) : { next : Void -> { value : Null<Dynamic>, key : String}, hasNext : Void -> Bool}

Given Hash, returns iterator to {key, value} pairs. Used in Render to iterate through Hash.

int_hash_to_key_value_iterable(s : IntHash<Dynamic>) : { next : Void -> { value : Null<Dynamic>, key : String}, hasNext : Void -> Bool}

Given IntHash, returns iterator to {key, value} pairs. Used in Render to iterate through IntHash.

object_to_key_value_iterable(s : Dynamic) : { next : Void -> { value : Dynamic, key : String}, hasNext : Void -> Bool}

Given object, returns iterator to {key, value} pairs. Used in Render to iterate through simple objects.

sort_by_keys(kv : Iterator<{ value : Dynamic, key : String}>) : Array<{ value : Dynamic, key : String}>

Given iterator to {key, value}, returns array with those {key, value} pairs, sorted by key.
